    "plan_content": "Here is the full implementation plan for the PulseBoard channel plugin.\n\n---\n\n## Plan Summary\n\n**7 new files** in `extensions/pulseboard/` — no existing files touched.\n\n### Key findings from codebase exploration\n\n**Pattern to follow:** Nostr (`extensions/nostr/`) is the closest reference — it's a simpler plugin that uses inline `meta`, the shorthand `outbound` adapter form, and builds the config adapter without a separate helper barrel.\n\n**Important constraint discovered:** `getChatChannelMeta(id)` only works with pre-registered `ChatChannelId` values from the core channel registry (e.g. `\"irc\"`, `\"nostr\"`, `\"telegram\"`). Since `\"pulseboard\"` is fictional and not registered there, calling it would fail both type-checking and at runtime. The plan imports it from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core` (per requirements) but builds the `meta` object inline — exactly as Nostr does.\n\n---\n\n### Files to create\n\n| File | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `extensions/pulseboard/package.json` | `@openclaw/pulseboard`, type `\"module\"`, full `openclaw` block |\n| `extensions/pulseboard/openclaw.plugin.json` | `id: \"pulseboard\"`, `channels: [\"pulseboard\"]`, minimal `configSchema` |\n| `extensions/pulseboard/src/types.ts` | `PulseBoardAccount`, `PulseBoardConfig`, `PulseBoardMessage` interfaces |\n| `extensions/pulseboard/src/runtime.ts` | `createPluginRuntimeStore<PluginRuntime>` → exports `getPulseBoardRuntime`, `setPulseBoardRuntime` |\n| `extensions/pulseboard/src/channel.ts` | `createChatChannelPlugin` with inline meta, stub config/setup/gateway, `normalizeTarget`, `outbound` using `attachChannelToResult` |\n| `extensions/pulseboard/index.ts` | `defineChannelPluginEntry` with id/name/description/plugin/setRuntime |\n| `extensions/pulseboard/setup-entry.ts` | `defineSetupPluginEntry(pulseBoardPlugin)` |\n\n### Verification steps\n1. `pnpm tsgo` — type-check passes\n2. `pnpm check` — lint/format passes\n3. `pnpm build` — build smoke passes with no dynamic import warnings",
